## Cache Architecture

`supabaseCache.ts` provides synchronous read/write via an in-memory `Map`. Writes debounce (300ms) and push to Supabase asynchronously via `pushToSupabase` (which includes `logSyncError` error handling for all operations). Realtime subscriptions on 15 tables auto-refresh the cache on remote changes (500ms debounce).

### ID Strategy
All new IDs use `crypto.randomUUID()`. Legacy timestamp IDs may exist in migrated data.

### Multi-Tenancy
Every table has `group_id`. RLS policies enforce isolation. `getGroupId()` from `supabaseCache.ts` provides the current group.

## Group Management SQL RPCs (`supabase/004-group-management.sql` + `008-multi-group.sql`)

13+ RPCs with owner-aware security. All sensitive operations check `groups.created_by`. Multi-group RPCs (008) accept optional `p_group_id` parameter with `DEFAULT NULL` for backward compatibility.

| RPC | Who Can Call | Purpose |
|-----|-------------|---------|
| `create_group(name, display_name)` | Any authenticated | Creates group + owner player + default settings |
| `join_group_by_invite(code, display_name)` | Any authenticated | Joins via invite code as `member` |
| `link_member_to_player(target_player_id)` | Any member | Links own account to existing player |
| `self_create_and_link(player_name)` | Any member | Creates player and links self |
| `update_member_role(target_user_id, new_role)` | Admin (owner for admin targets) | Changes role |
| `remove_group_member(target_user_id)` | Admin (owner for admin targets) | Removes member |
| `transfer_ownership(new_owner_id)` | Owner only | Transfers ownership |
| `regenerate_invite_code()` | Owner only | New invite code |
| `create_player_invite(target_player_id)` | Admin | Personal invite tied to player |
| `join_group_by_player_invite(code, display_name)` | Any authenticated | Joins via personal invite |
| `unlink_member_player(target_user_id)` | Admin | Unlinks member from player |
| `add_member_by_email(target_email, target_player_id)` | Admin | Adds user by email |
| `fetch_group_members_with_email()` | Admin | Member list with emails |

## API Key Flow

```
Owner sets keys in Settings > AI tab
  тЖТ Saved to `settings` table (gemini_api_key / elevenlabs_api_key)
  тЖТ Cache maps via toSettings/settingsToRow (includes API key fields)
  тЖТ Client reads via getSettings()?.geminiApiKey
  тЖТ Sent in proxy request body to Vercel Edge Functions
  тЖТ Edge Function: request body key > env var fallback > error
```

